[3]
Date: Mon 1 Aug 2005
From: Pablo Nart <pablo11@hotPOP.com>
Source: El Pais, Spain [edited]
<http://www.elpais.es/articulo/elpporsoc/20050801elpepusoc_3/Tes>

More than 400 cases of salmonella after eating pre-cooked chicken
-----------------------------------------------
The 9 communities affected have confirmed a total of 417 cases.
Murcia is the community with the higher number of affected people
(113), followed by Andalucia (78), Castilla-La Mancha (68), Comunidad
Valenciana (55), Cataluna (42), La Rioja (20), Baleares (20), Aragon
(14) and Madrid (9) (The contributor notes that these represent most
of peninsular Spain other than the northern Atlantic coast. -
Mod.LL). Although the Spanish Ministry of Health has recognized 30
outbreaks so far, with 120 confirmed cases, it is awaiting
epidemiological investigations before issuing final figures of
affected cases.
The infections are linked to pre-cooked chicken Pollo Asado Sada y
Pollo Asado Pimpollo. The products were recalled by the manufacturer
Grupo Sada.
Jose Ignacio Arranz, Director of the Spanish Agency for Food Safety
(Agencia Espanola de Seguridad Alimentaria, AESA), has said that the
pipes of the sauce dispenser used to season the chicken were the
original source. Grupo Sada has corroborated this information in an
official statement.
--
Pablo Nart
<pablo11@hotPOP.com>
[ProMED thanks Pablo Nart for calling our attention to this
substantial outbreak of salmonellosis. The serotype (or serotypes) of
_S. enterica_ involved are not stated. - Mod.LL]
